nd Windows.\n- Make capture idempotent enough for repeated invocations against the same\n  transcript file.\n- Return a concise capture report suitable for CLI JSON output and hook logs.\n\n## Later Goals\n\nThese remain valid ideas, but should not block the POC:\n\n- Capture the current or recent AI coding session without an explicit path.\n- Add Claude Code behind the same crate boundary after\n[TRUNCATED]\nfault target should be `project` unless a target is explicit.\n- Branch or commit inference should be added later, after hook payloads and\n  GitButler workspace semantics are clearer.\n- The command should capture only new transcript records when possible.\n- The command should preserve transcript records as JSONL-compatible strings only\n  when `--include-transcript` is set.\n- The command should record provenance fields such as provider, model, tool,\n  session id, source path, and capture timestamp when available.\n- The command should tolerate partially written transcript files.\n- The command should produce human-readable output by default and structured JSON\n  when invoked through the existing CLI JSON mode.\n\n## Quality Requirements\n\n- Keep the new crate independent from legacy virtual-branch APIs.\n- Keep lower-level logic independent of `but-api`.\n- Prefer `gix` or existing repository handles for repository inspection.\n- For the POC, use structured parsing for Codex JSONL from an explicit path.\n- Future agents may require structured parsing for SQLite or other sources.\n- Future platform-specific path discovery should stay isolated in agent modules.\n- Make freshness and deduplication testable with injected clocks and fixture\n  directories.\n- Add narrow tests for agent location, transcript parsing, deduplication, and\n  GitMeta write planning.\n\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- After the POC, should capture default to `branch:<current-name>` or `project`\n  when no explicit target is provided?\n- Should raw transcript contents be captured by default